description: For sale: $290,000. This lovely home is in a perfect location near Medicine Lake, and the heart of Plymouth. The front yard looks out to a quiet street. This well cared for home has hard wood floors throughout and three bedrooms on the main level.  It also has a large open floor plan for the kitchen, dining room and living room.  The lower level has a multi-use room that is currently an additional family room but is ready to be converted into a fourth bedroom.  New roof just installed in April 2020.  Home is just a few short blocks from West Medicine Lake Park and the great trail systems you can enjoy from there.  This is a great home and location to move in and make your own.

description:
For sale: $289,900. Email: churchillap@gmail.com
Wilderness retreat three blocks from West Medicine Lake Park. WAYZATA SCHOOL DISTRICT! New exterior paint - 2018. New interior paint, trim, and baseboards throughout - 2019. Updated upper level flooring - 2017. Newer lower level walkout with full bath. 4 bedrooms - 3 large bedrooms with the 4th currently turned into a walk-in closet just off the master. Large lot with beautiful landscaping, garden shed, fire pit, and a NEW DECK built in 2019! Peacefully surrounded by nature, walking/bike paths, and West Medicine Lake Beach! (Still need to post Master bedroom picture). The Street View pics are old and outdated. This property is very well maintained and a must see at this price range!

description: For sale: $449,900. Welcome home to 10635 34th Ave! This home has everything you've been dreaming of: an open floor plan, a bright, newly remodeled kitchen; 4 bedrooms, 3 baths; a mudroom; and plenty of space for you and your family's needs. Hardwood floors in the main level, tile in the mud room. This home is ideal for entertaining. The large kitchen features granite countertops, a prominent island, with seating for six, and a wall oven.  The kitchen opens to a separate dining and living room with gas fireplace.  The living room and dining room windows overlook a private backyard with mature trees for privacy. Three bedrooms on the main-level, with a large master suite. The master bath features dual sinks, allowing for plenty of space and travertine tile. Get out and enjoy the outdoors!  Quick 10 min drive to downtown Minneapolis. Heated tile floor in mud room.This home is 1.5 blocks to Medicine Lake, with easy access to the Medicine Lake Regional trail system.

Coming soon: $340,000. Incredible family home in great neighborhood is move-in ready! Welcoming open floor plan with gorgeous original hardwoods throughout. Updates in kitchen include carefree vinyl flooring, stainless appliances. Great cabinet storage, plus bonus breakfast bar. Sliding doors lead to deck which overlooks amazing fenced backyard. Informal dining off kitchen. Updated interior paint and lighting. Bonus finished porch has ceramic tile floors and wood ceiling for that cozy feel. Updated full bath with ceramic tile, double vanity. Finished, full walkout basement has family room with gas fireplace, brick surround, additional bedroom, plus 3/4 bath with new vanity and flooring. Spacious storage and laundry area. Attached two-car garage. Nearby Medicine Lake, Clifton French Regional Park. EZ access to Hwy 169.  For more information on this listing before it goes on the market, please reach out to our Listing Manager,Laurie, at laurie@kerbyandcristina.com.

For sale: $325,000. You had me at screen porch! Low maintenance living with the perks of a single-family home! No mowing, snow removal, garbage included! $20K of recent improvements. Fresh paint, new carpet and plank flooring. Owner took great care to ready this home for market. Highlighted feature: two bedrooms up, two on the main. Bathroom on each level. Two family rooms on lower level! Ample storage area also has work bench.

description: For sale: $385,000. Great Plymouth Location near Lost Lake. Your opportunity to own this well maintained 4BR,3BA,2CAR home on .40 acre lot in a great neighborhood. Updated in 2008, this home has a spacious Entry, Maple Hardwood Flooring, large Living Room, Formal & Informal Dining. The Kitchen was updated w/Maple Cabinets, Granite Counter-tops, Tile back-splash, Under-cabinet lighting & SS Appliances. 3 Bedrooms on the Upper Level w/shared Full Bath. Master has its own 3/4 Private Bath. Head downstairs to a Cozy Family Room w/builtin's, Gas Fireplace & Walkout to a wonderful 3-Season Porch and enjoy the backyard Patio. There is also a 4th Bedroom, 3/4 Bath & large Utility/Laundry Room.  The lower level has more opportunity for additional FSF, a workshop & more.  Recent Updates: LP Siding/Trim/Soffit/Gutters (2019), Concrete Driveway (2017), Remodel & All New Windows (2008). Close to Clifton French Park, Trails & Medicine Lake. Super location for shopping, schools & commute 169/494. This home is a Gem!

Coming soon: $510,000. Charm & elegance with impressive updates throughout. This is an exceptional home in every sense of the word and truly shows like a model- meticulously maintained and loved. Enjoy entertaining in the spacious kitchen featuring large center island, granite counters, and endless storage which opens to large family room and tranquil sunroom overlooking picturesque park like setting and pool. Head upstairs to four beds/2bath including spacious Master Suite perfect for relaxing! Walkout lower level boasts huge family room with fireplace perfect for cozy winters, bonus game area, additional bedroom and more. Prime south facing lot & custom landscaping borders extensive trail system that leads to 3 parks!
For more information on this listing before it goes on the market, please reach out to our Listing Manager, Laurie Jones, at laurie@kerbyandcristina.com.

description: For sale: $1,200,000. This gorgeous and conveniently located Medicine Lake front home has almost 60' of sandy lakeshore and is on the Luce Line Trail in the heart of Plymouth.The home boasts expansive views of the lake with oversized windows and multi level decking.  Upon entering you are greeted with thoughtfully defined, yet open spaces that are functional and perfect for entertaining including an amazing sound system both inside and out. Main level billiard room is built to potentially be a 4th bedroom for all main level living capability.  Natural light beams off the Brazilian tiger cherry floors, cherry cabinetry and maple woodwork. All new carpet and fresh paint making it truly turn key. Spacious master suite has picturesque lake views with a private deck, vaulted ceilings, double sided fireplace, heated floors, custom walk in shower and whirlpool tub. Infrared heated garage with 10 foot doors and a 12,000lb hoist make this a car connoisseurs dream.  Fully equipped with a 62 ft dock and boat lift.

description: For sale: $399,900. This lovely Plymouth two story sits on a quiet cul-de-sac and corner lot, half a mile from schools, shopping, restaurants and highway access, and several parks. Beautiful updates throughout, including countertops, appliances and flooring. The outdoor living spaces are a highlight--just in time for spring and summer! The 4-season porch opens to a 2-year-old maintenance-free deck, which walks down to a second deck on the ground level, as well as a gorgeous paver patio with fire pit! In-ground irrigation covers entire yard. Recreational opportunities abound.  You're within walking distance from Three Rivers French Regional Park and Mission Hills Park with a playground.  You're also 1 mile from Medicine Lake and all of its walking/biking trails. Don't miss this one!

For sale: $349,900. Welcome home to this charming Cape Cod just steps from Medicine Lake's West Park/Beach. 3 bed 2 bath with main floor owner's suite and walk-in-closet! Sunny updated granite and stainless kitchen, cozy family room with gas fireplace plus well-appointed formal living and dining rooms. Beautiful hardwood floors throughout. New paver patio and fire pit, perfect for entertaining on the quiet wooded lot. 20 minutes from Downtown Minneapolis with express bus only one block away. Hundreds of miles of scenic walk/bike trails outside your front door. Features 3+ garage stalls and Wayzata schools! Full of character, you will not want to miss!  ***CLICK ON 3D TOUR LINK FOR VIRTUAL SHOWING!

description:
For sale: $725,000. Enjoy beautiful sunsets over Medicine Lake from the deck of your new home, where you'll enjoy the benefits of lake living without the lakeshore taxes. There is 100+ feet of private use lakeshore (dock is allowed) just across Medicine Lake Boulevard, which is a quiet, one-way street with low traffic volume. 

Also, just off-shore in front of the home, you can walk or ride your bike along the 16-mile paved Medicine Lake Regional Trail, which connects Elm Creek Park Reserve in Maple Grove with French Regional Park and the Luce Line State Trail in Plymouth. 

If lounging is more your style, grab a cold beverage and head out to the in-ground, heated pool where relaxation is taken to a whole new level. Never owned a pool before? Don't worry! This pool is virtually maintenance-free with new pool heater, filter pump, liner, and automated skimmer kit!

With an open floor plan, updated kitchen, and a separate bedroom and bathroom tucked away from it all, this is a perfect home for entertaining or hosting weekend guests. Just think of the Summertime barbecues you could have in your new lake home! 

Imagine a bar downstairs and maybe a pool table and big-screen TV there's even an area for a hot tub near the sauna. Need a little workout inspiration? You could use that space for your treadmill or elliptical machine, which gives you a perfect view of the lake during your workout!

The commute will be a short one this home is only 10 miles from Minneapolis and 20 miles from St. Paul! You won't have the daily hassle of fighting traffic like you would experience with other popular lakes in the western suburbs.

There's nothing to do but move in and, believe it or not, Summer's right around the corner!

Well maintained exterior with brand new roof and concrete driveway, rear of home has new siding, extensive landscaping including walkways, retaining walls, colorful gardens and perennials; large south facing deck overlooks private wooded backyard. 1 BLOCK TO MEDICINE LAKE with pathways that lead to French Park.

Recently sold: $220,000. Complete info: http://1253024thave.IsNow4Sale.com - Nestled on a quiet, tree-lined street, the curb appeal and charm of this home will delight any new homeowner. Conveniently located in a great neighborhood near Medicine Lake, the locale of this home is second to none in the area.  Spacious and inviting, the main level of this one level home can accommodate a variety of lifestyles. The updated flooring and abundance of natural light set the stage for the living room - perfect for entertaining. The wonderful eat-in kitchen has been nicely updated and looks into the fully fenced in backyard. Two charming bedrooms and a full bathrooms complete this level.   Make your way downstairs to the lower level featuring a great family room with newer carpet and recessed lighting, one bedroom, a den/office area, an updated bathroom, and a large laundry room.   Any new owner will appreciate the new roof, newer main level windows, and newer water softener. description: Recently sold: $305,000. This house is a one of a kind, well cared for mid-century modern home. It boasts vaulted ceilings,3 bedrooms & 2 baths on the main level, plenty of closet space & teak kitchen cabinets. The backyard consists of a large deck, medium tree coverage, perennial gardens & storage/wood shed. The walkout, permanent wood foundation, keeps the basement warm in winter and cool in summer. It includes a 4th bedroom, cedar bathroom with sauna, & a 2nd kitchen. There is a 2 car heated garage w/full attic. The house is situated on a quiet street centered between Hwy 55 & 394. It is blocks away from a park & ride, Wayzata East Middle School & Sunset Elementary. Shopping, dining, The YMCA, & the Medicine Lake Regional Trail are within a 3 mile radius. Owning this house means you would be in one of the top rated school districts, 20 minutes away from downtown Minneapolis, & a short drive away from either Medicine Lake or Lake Minnetonka. Make this unique home your forever home.

description:
Recently sold: $222,500. Beautiful, fully remodeled, stand-alone townhome with the feel of a private single-family home! Open, airy floor plan, with newer windows and lots of light. Large FULLY REMODELED kitchen with new appliances, newly tiled walls, and new kitchen cabinets and countertops. Additional china cabinet wall in the dining room. Large private deck with pergola facing a wooded view with lots of privacy. Large master bedroom with lots of closet space. 2 bedrooms and a separate bathroom on each level - nice for a group of roommates, or kids who want some independence. Cozy lower level family room. Separate laundry room with cabinets and work surface.
2 car attached garage plus plenty of street parking. ENORMOUS lawn area just steps from the house - perfect for a family or pets! Extremely well-managed association, with a private heated pool, large private clubhouse, playground, and basketball court. This one won't last long, so e-mail or text to arrange a showing.

Landscaping & snow removal included FREE! Lease term and move-in date flexible.

description: Recently sold: $435,000. Amazing mid century modern one story home just steps to Medicine Lake. Renovated gourmet kitchen with new hardwood floors, custom cabinetry, backsplash and stainless steel Bosch appliances. Master suite with 3/4 bath and walk in closet. Two fireplaces, large 3 season porch overlooking a private wooded lot with views of the lake. Large deck, updated bathrooms, large family room and amusement room along with a 4th bedroom, exercise room, and 3/4 bathroom in the walkout lower level. New Timberline roof 2018, 3 stage reverse osmosis filter system. Large .3 acre lot connects to city owned land makes this private, wooded lot seem like it's over an acre.

Recently sold: $290,200. Private cul-de-sac location with loads of charm! Upper level living room with amazing natural light. Kitchen features stainless steel appliances, stone countertops, updated hardware and eat-in kitchen. Owner's suite has private 3/4 bath and great closets. Finished lower level boasts large family room with gas fireplace, plus huge wet bar and game room. Spacious laundry with storage. Wooded backyard includes stone patio, and space to entertain. Two-car garage with storage galore. Nearby Pilgrim Lane Elementary Park and Lost Lake.

Recently sold: $505,000. Rare opportunity to own this one-level, one owner detached walk-out villa home located in the small community of the Courtyards of French Creek! This highly sought after friendly community backs up to French Regional Park with immediate access. Features include a spacious, open floor plan with inviting large foyer with maple flooring, main floor great room with gas fireplace, master suite with large walk-in closet, updated kitchen with white cabinets, granite counter tops, stainless steel appliances and additional office/2nd bedroom on the same level. The walk-out lower level includes a large family room with 2nd gas fireplace, 3rd bedroom with walk in closet, 3/4 bath, and wet bar with wine refrigerator. Enjoy your maintenance free deck, with shade awning, overlooking the community pond, 3 car garage with access to lower level, low association dues and many social opportunities, if desired.

description: Recently sold: $351,000. This fantastic 3-bedroom home has great space inside and out. Your first steps bring you into the living room with vaulted ceiling & gorgeous wood beams. The bay windows & hardwood floors show off the charm found here. The fully remodeled kitchen has beautiful white cabinets, granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, farmhouse style sink, subway tile backsplash, & loads of storage. The formal dining room is open to the kitchen & living room making it great for entertaining. You'll love the hardwood floors found throughout many rooms including all 3 bedrooms. All the bedrooms are located upstairs with a full bathroom as well as a private master bath. description:
Recently sold: $385,000. Gorgeous split level family home nestled in charming cul-de-sac freshly updated throughout means you?ve found THE one! Oversized foyer leads upstairs to open kitchen/dining and spacious living room anchored by gorgeous gas fireplace perfect for snuggling up! Natural light pours in from huge windows surrounding the home. Enjoy morning coffee in large sunroom off the dining. Two bedrooms, full bath and spacious Master Suite round off the ML. Head downstairs to bright family room with gas fireplace with game area, in addition to 3/4 bath, laundry and storage. Private backyard is begging for family fun and BBQ?s with huge deck, sports court and landscaping. Nearby Clifton E French Regional Park and trails.

For more information on this listing before it goes on the market, please reach out to our Listing Manager, Emilie Waletich, at emilie@kerbyandcristina.com.  No PreMLS Showings.

Bright, open and spacious, located only minutes from Downtown! Gorgeous hardwoods are framed out by 9-foot ceilings and glisten with natural light pouring in from huge windows throughout the home. Spacious living room opens to kitchen and dining perfect for Holiday gatherings with a gas fireplace. Head upstairs to three bedrooms, loft, and large full bath featuring a jetted tub begging for relaxation. Finished lower level includes family room, large lookout windows, laundry room and bonus storage area. Enjoy your morning coffee or host a BBQ out back on deck overlooking wooded creek. Nearby paths, Bassett Creek and fantastic shopping/dining!

description:
Recently sold: $322,500. Contact Linda Hamilton @ lahmcfan@yahoo.com
Phone   937-477-4766  
I am having trouble with getting pictures loaded.   More coming!  
No solicitations and no agents asking to list.   We have a selling agent if we decide to sell with a realtor.

You and your family will love this great home with all its charm and character nestled on a beautiful private wooded lot in the Wilshire Gardens neighborhood of Plymouth.  Lovingly maintained with lots of modern updates and generous sized rooms throughout the home.  This home is ready for your family to move in and enjoy all 3150++ finished sq. feet just in time for summer Bar-B-Q's!

You will really appreciate the gleaming hardwood floors throughout the main floor office, family room, dining area and kitchen.  Great entertaining space throughout the kitchen and adjoining family room with fireplace.

Nice entry to the home with staircase to the second level and open to the large main living room.

The first floor family room has an energy efficient wood burning fireplace and access to the 3-season porch.  You'll appreciate the large kitchen with modern appliances and convenient breakfast bar.  Tons of cabinets and plenty of counter space.  Convenient formal dining room right off the kitchen area makes entertaining something you'll want to do often!  

Mom and Dad, you'll love the main floor master bedroom with adjoining  dressing room and large closet.  Upper level is finished with 3 generous sized bedrooms and another full bathroom.  Two bedrooms have dormers giving this space some real character.  

The lower level is finished with a huge rec-room where you can set up your favorite billiard and game tables.  Nice 3/4 bath with shower, nice laundry room with extra storage space, too.   The lower level also has a 5th bedroom!

This home lends itself well to wheel chair accessibility if needed through the back entrance.

The yard has lots of lovely perennials and lots of large trees.  The back yard has a nice southern open space.   Everyone will enjoy the 3-season porch and huge deck where you can watch the kids, grill some dinner & entertain friends and family all summer long! 

Attached 2+ car garage.  Third garage would make a great shop area or extra storage for all your big toys.  In fact, the basement rec-room would also make a great in home work shop for anyone who likes to do woodworking, quilting, painting, any kind of building or crafty projects.

Close to local Wayzata schools, parks, walking trails, shopping, restaurants and major highways making your commute very easy.

Custom gourmet kitchen showcases gorgeous quartz countertops, a glass and stone-tile backsplash, stainless steel appliances, and high-end maple cabinetry with undermount lighting and several custom pull outs. This wonderful property is located in a great community just steps from French Regional Park and Medicine Lake.

Recently sold: $500,000. Love the charm and character of the early 20th century, but don't want to live in the city? This is the home for you! This is 1920's farmhouse is nicely updated and situated on a beautifully landscaped half-acre lot is close to Ridgedale, Hopkins Crossroad, and 394 and just minutes to Downtown Minneapolis. Some of the features and updates include:	

?	Hardwood floors, crown moulding, and gorgeous original woodwork.
?	Wonderful main level floor plan with large rooms, wood burning fireplace, formal dining, sunroom and large front porch.
?	4 bedrooms plus a sleeping porch on the upper level. 
?	Updated eat in kitchen has custom cabinetry, new bay window, high-end stainless appliances and granite countertops. 
?	Updated bathrooms with custom tile in lower and whirlpool tub in upper level.
?	Newer roof and boiler.
?	Finished family room in the lower level plus additional finish-able attic space allows you to expand and build equity.
?	Heated 3-car garage has separate electrical service and ventilation system. 
?	3 porches and large paver patio overlooking the large yard and perennial gardens.
?	In-ground sprinkler and home security systems already installed.
?	Wayzata school district!

description: Recently sold: $355,000. First month's rent and security deposit (one month's rent) required to secure property. No pets. No smoking. All applications due Friday 7/26/19 at 6:00 PM Central Time. Immaculate luxury townhouse in beautiful setting. Open main level floor plan with tons of natural light. High-end kitchen features hardwood floors, large island, granite counters, and stainless steel appliances. Dining area has pond views. Private patio. 3 bedrooms on upper level. Master suite features walk-in closet, large bathroom with seperate tub and shower, and private balcony with pond views. Upper level loft area. Upper level laundry. Gas fireplace. Main level powder room. 2-car garage. Large, two-story foyer. Irrigation system. Every room freshly painted. Outstanding location. One block to Luce Line trail and very close to Medicine Lake. Easy highway access. Close to shopping and restaurants. Wayzata schools. Absolutely move-in ready. Check out the virtual tour!

description: Recently sold: $80,000. Call 612-812-4174 or email dornleasing@ renterswarehouse.com to schedule a showing, do not use showmojo. Available now! $500 rent credit if rented 12/1 or sooner!  Prime Plymouth location! Access to Medicine Lake and the Luce Line trail! Inquire about the opportunity for a dock slip! Enjoy the outdoor pool, tennis court, basketball court and exercise room. Short 10-minute drive to downtown Minneapolis. The unit has been completely remodeled! New laminate flooring throughout, newer appliances, kitchen cabinets, paint, and several bathroom updates! There is a separate dining area off the kitchen which accommodates a large dining table. Spacious living room with access to a private deck overlooking stunning Medicine Lake! Large master bedroom with a walk-in closet. Full bath. Rent includes a heated underground parking spot and ample overflow lot parking. All utilities included except electric. Surrounding areas: Golden Valley, New Hope, St. Louis Park, Minneapolis, Wayzata.

description: Recently sold: $316,000. Immaculate 2-story home tucked in a wooded cul-de-sac. Large slate floor entry welcomes you into the open main floor. Large newer windows let in lots of natural light. 3 bedrooms on the upper level. Private 3/4 shower in the master. Lots of storage in the unfinished basement. Garage is heated and has an epoxy finished floor. Large back yard with storage shed and irrigation system. Easy access to major roadways, shopping and parks.
